  "texts": [
    "In addition, the role of unsupervised pre-training in natural language processing, especially for texts that are unclassified or not tied to specific categories, has become increasingly significant.",
    "By using text such as abstracts and titles for the computation of the embedding, these methods could not only offer future utility for datasets lacking tags, but also allow researchers to disambiguate trajectories that have limited self-reported information.",
    "We note however some limitations.",
    "While advanced models like deep learning and transformer-based ones can decipher complex, non-linear data relationships, they present interpretational challenges [64], leading to a reduction in the explainability that our method using annotated tags offers.",
    "Moreover, while potentially gaining in predictive power, such embeddings generally reduce very high dimensional data (eg, text, images, etc) to not-so-low-dimensional spaces (dozens of dimensions), which would be of less interest for the comparison with mobility data that is our focus here.Our work is focused on a dataset of arXiv pre-prints."
  ],
